1
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:21,880
Mr. Yuan,

2
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,520
you've been dumping
Minghui shares lately.

3
00:00:25,680 --> 00:00:26,880
Guess you've got cash

4
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:28,880
to burn on charity now.

5
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:35,600
What are you looking at?

6
00:00:36,200 --> 00:00:38,200
Can't I chat with Mr. Yuan?

7
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:49,480
Even if Xu Wanxin
puts up something worth a fortune...

8
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,400
Even if Xu Wanxin
puts up something worth a fortune tonight,

9
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:57,600
it won't make a difference.

10
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:01,600
In the end, it all depends on my dad
whether he's willing to do her this favor.

11
00:01:03,720 --> 00:01:05,440
A no-sale at an auction

12
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:07,600
will indeed make headlines.

13
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:12,560
Just wait.

14
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:15,000
Once my plan works tonight,

15
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:17,440
everything will fall back into place.

16
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:22,640
Hao, don't do anything reckless.

17
00:01:23,400 --> 00:01:25,800
I won't be able to cover for you
if you go too far.

18
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,840
Just sit back and watch.

19
00:01:33,020 --> 00:01:36,700
=Echoes of Gang City=

20
00:01:36,860 --> 00:01:41,500
=Episode 7=
(Heartbeats and Breaths Fall into Sync)

21
00:01:41,758 --> 00:01:45,038
(Utmost Brightness &amp; Radiance Charity Gala)
Welcome to Minghui Group's charity gala.

22
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:47,480
This gala dates back
to the Republican era

23
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:50,400
and has been carried on
for over a century by Mr. Xu Qianmo.

24
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:53,600
Now, let's welcome tonight's host.

25
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:57,200
Ms. Xu Wanxin,
interim chairwoman of Minghui Group,

26
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:58,600
and her husband, Mr. Shen Gu,

27
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:01,200
will open the auction.

28
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:02,960
A round of applause, please.

29
00:02:49,490 --> 00:02:50,760
Good evening, everyone.

30
00:02:51,570 --> 00:02:52,680
I'm Xu Wanxin.

31
00:02:56,780 --> 00:02:58,260
Thank you for being here.

32
00:02:58,660 --> 00:03:00,700
This is my first time

33
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:02,060
hosting this charity gala

34
00:03:02,380 --> 00:03:04,580
on behalf of my grandfather, Xu Qianmo.

35
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:07,580
Whether it's children in remote areas,

36
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:09,980
elderly people in hardship,

37
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:12,660
or those fighting illness,

38
00:03:13,180 --> 00:03:16,380
they gain a little more strength
because we are gathered here.

39
00:03:16,580 --> 00:03:17,980
They gain a little more light

40
00:03:18,980 --> 00:03:20,180
because of our kindness.

41
00:03:20,980 --> 00:03:23,300
I now declare

42
00:03:24,060 --> 00:03:26,380
"Utmost Brightness and Radiance"
Charity Gala

43
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:28,060
officially open.

44
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:37,580
Thank you, everyone.

45
00:03:40,100 --> 00:03:40,780
Thank you.

46
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:44,380
Thank you for your wonderful speech,
Miss Xu Wanxin.

47
00:03:44,380 --> 00:03:47,020
Let's give her a round of applause.
Thank you. Please have a seat.

48
00:03:48,780 --> 00:03:49,980
Over the years,

49
00:03:50,180 --> 00:03:52,260
we've witnessed countless miracles.

50
00:03:53,020 --> 00:03:55,580
Tonight, our first auction item

51
00:03:55,580 --> 00:03:58,860
is provided by Ms. Xu Wanxin
of Minghui Group.

52
00:03:59,020 --> 00:04:01,300
It is a painting collected
by the late Mr. Xu Zhaoming.

53
00:04:01,300 --> 00:04:03,780
Created by the renowned
Ming dynasty artist,

54
00:04:03,780 --> 00:04:07,020
Qin Xiyuan.

55
00:04:07,460 --> 00:04:09,020
"Viewing Phoenix Tower".

56
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:10,980
Dated 1550.

57
00:04:11,180 --> 00:04:14,860
Measuring 113.5 by 41.5 centimeters.

58
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:18,180
It bears inscriptions
of "Viewing Phoenix Tower"

59
00:04:18,620 --> 00:04:19,900
and the seals

60
00:04:19,980 --> 00:04:23,180
from both Mr. Xu Zhaoming
and Mr. Xu Qianmo,

61
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:26,580
reflecting its history and legacy.

62
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:29,500
The starting bid is 15 million

63
00:04:29,660 --> 00:04:31,980
with each increment of 1 million.

64
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:34,780
The starting bid is 15 million

65
00:04:34,780 --> 00:04:37,380
with each increment of 1 million.

66
00:04:37,780 --> 00:04:39,420
Let's start. Here we go.

67
00:04:46,820 --> 00:04:49,380
If this were at Christie's,

68
00:04:49,380 --> 00:04:51,980
it'd be snapped up in seconds.

69
00:04:52,300 --> 00:04:54,220
It's a top-tier collectible.

70
00:04:54,220 --> 00:04:56,060
What a pity.

71
00:04:59,820 --> 00:05:02,780
We can't spend money
to support our enemy, can we?

72
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:05,300
Tempting as it is. Better hold back.

73
00:05:13,380 --> 00:05:15,380
16 million once.

74
00:05:16,260 --> 00:05:17,900
16 million twice.

75
00:05:20,180 --> 00:05:21,220
Anyone else?

76
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:29,420
17 million once.

77
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:33,580
17 million twice.

78
00:05:33,580 --> 00:05:34,780
One last time.

79
00:05:35,820 --> 00:05:37,100
Congratulations.

80
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:38,700
The painting "Viewing Phoenix Tower"

81
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:41,180
by Chinese artist Qin Xiyuan

82
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:43,180
goes to Ms. Song Qionghua.

83
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:52,220
Our second item tonight
is a Han Dynasty Jade Bixie Amulet.

84
00:05:52,460 --> 00:05:54,620
Made of Hetian jade

85
00:05:54,620 --> 00:05:58,180
with a smooth and lustrous texture.

86
00:05:58,180 --> 00:06:01,420
Some areas show calcification
with a yellow-brown patina.

87
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:05,020
The starting bid is 16 million.

88
00:06:05,620 --> 00:06:07,900
The starting bid is 16 million

89
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:10,500
with each increment of 1 million.

90
00:06:11,660 --> 00:06:13,780
Why bring out such a worthless rock

91
00:06:13,780 --> 00:06:15,300
to embarrass yourselves?

92
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:19,020
This item isn't appealing.

93
00:06:19,260 --> 00:06:21,180
That's nonsense.

94
00:06:21,420 --> 00:06:23,100
A Ming dynasty artist's painting.

95
00:06:23,260 --> 00:06:24,820
A Han dynasty jade amulet.

96
00:06:25,100 --> 00:06:27,900
They're highly sought after at auctions.

97
00:06:28,380 --> 00:06:30,980
Mr. Haoran, surely you can tell?

98
00:06:31,780 --> 00:06:33,780
I don't like how you're putting it.

99
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:35,340
Whether an item is good or not

100
00:06:35,340 --> 00:06:37,380
should be decided by bidders.

101
00:06:38,180 --> 00:06:41,820
Miss Xu can't bring out a decent item,
and now you're blaming us?

102
00:06:43,020 --> 00:06:44,380
You have such high standards.

103
00:06:44,380 --> 00:06:45,300
Tell us.

104
00:06:45,420 --> 00:06:46,820
What counts as a good item?

105
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:51,260
I think Miss Xu's necklace
is quite nice.

106
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:53,020
European royal jewelry.

107
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:55,180
It's collected by Mr. Xu Qiaomo
from the Republican era.

108
00:06:55,340 --> 00:06:56,500
If Miss Xu

109
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:59,180
is willing to put it up for auction,

110
00:06:59,180 --> 00:07:02,620
I'll offer a round number.

111
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:11,260
Since this is her first charity gala,

112
00:07:11,260 --> 00:07:14,380
it'd make it even more meaningful.

113
00:07:14,580 --> 00:07:17,060
What do you all think?

114
00:07:18,660 --> 00:07:19,460
Right.

115
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:21,300
Sounds good.

116
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:22,780
You think it's good?

117
00:07:23,180 --> 00:07:24,900
Why don't you put up
your own family heirloom?

118
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:27,660
So, Miss Xu won't put it up?

119
00:07:29,460 --> 00:07:30,700
Seems this so-called charity

120
00:07:30,940 --> 00:07:33,660
is just for show.

121
00:07:54,980 --> 00:07:55,820
Silence, please.

122
00:07:57,780 --> 00:08:00,660
This necklace was a coming-of-age gift

123
00:08:01,420 --> 00:08:03,020
from my grandfather
when I turned 18.

124
00:08:04,060 --> 00:08:05,700
It means a lot to me.

125
00:08:07,060 --> 00:08:07,860
But

126
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:10,780
if

127
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:14,020
it can contribute

128
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:15,780
to Minghui's charity effort,

129
00:08:16,580 --> 00:08:18,620
I believe that's what my grandfather
would've wanted.

130
00:08:43,500 --> 00:08:46,620
Your cufflink matches
Miss Wanxin's necklace well.

131
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,620
It's a gift from her.

132
00:09:00,420 --> 00:09:02,780
An 18-carat Tear of Ocean sapphire,

133
00:09:02,780 --> 00:09:03,900
A stone representing love.

134
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:05,100
It's of rare quality.

135
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:07,420
According to Mr. Xu Qianmo,

136
00:09:07,820 --> 00:09:11,300
this necklace was an engagement gift
from a patriotic businessman

137
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:12,980
in the Republic era to his fiancée.

138
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:22,620
The starting bid is 100 million.
Each increment is 10 million.

139
00:09:23,580 --> 00:09:26,820
The starting bid is 100 million

140
00:09:26,820 --> 00:09:30,700
with each subsequent increace
starting at 10 million.

141
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:34,020
Here we go.

142
00:09:38,260 --> 00:09:39,060
Mr. Haoran.

143
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:41,580
110 million.

144
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:44,020
Anyone else?

145
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:51,060
Mr. Shen Gu.

146
00:09:51,470 --> 00:09:53,180
120 million.

147
00:09:53,980 --> 00:09:55,060
Thank you, Mr. Shen Gu.

148
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:00,660
Mr. Shen Hao.

149
00:10:00,660 --> 00:10:03,020
130 million.

150
00:10:05,060 --> 00:10:09,220
140 million from Mr. Shen Gu.

151
00:10:15,860 --> 00:10:16,660
Mr. Shen Gu.

152
00:10:16,660 --> 00:10:18,380
200 million.

153
00:10:24,580 --> 00:10:27,820
That's the highest premium
for this diamond necklace.

154
00:10:28,660 --> 00:10:29,580
Mr. Shen Hao.

155
00:10:29,780 --> 00:10:32,980
Shen Gu is willing to waste money
on charity,

156
00:10:33,460 --> 00:10:34,580
but know your limits.

157
00:10:36,780 --> 00:10:38,060
Thank you, Mr. Shen Hao.

158
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:40,380
210 million.

159
00:10:53,980 --> 00:10:55,100
Mr. Shen Gu.

160
00:10:56,180 --> 00:10:58,180
300 million.

161
00:11:13,380 --> 00:11:15,260
300 million once.

162
00:11:24,180 --> 00:11:25,980
300 million twice.

163
00:11:30,900 --> 00:11:32,780
300 million thrice.

164
00:11:37,460 --> 00:11:39,900
Congratulations, Mr. Shen Gu.

165
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:47,380
Tear of Ocean is yours.

166
00:12:14,060 --> 00:12:14,780
Where is he going?

167
00:12:15,820 --> 00:12:16,740
No idea.

168
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:23,580
What are you doing?

169
00:12:29,380 --> 00:12:30,060
Don't move.

170
00:12:35,820 --> 00:12:36,620
Bravo!

171
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,380
What's going on?

172
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:46,500
Shut up.

173
00:12:55,980 --> 00:12:56,580
Bravo!

174
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:57,900
Bravo!

175
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:58,910
Bravo!

176
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:33,820
Shen Gu,

177
00:13:35,420 --> 00:13:37,100
thank you so much.

178
00:13:39,660 --> 00:13:41,060
I should return it to...

179
00:13:41,300 --> 00:13:41,860
No need.

180
00:13:54,380 --> 00:13:55,780
It matches my cufflink perfectly.

181
00:13:56,860 --> 00:13:59,620
It's a gift in return.

182
00:14:03,380 --> 00:14:04,060
Thank you.

183
00:14:07,260 --> 00:14:08,100
I thought

184
00:14:11,300 --> 00:14:12,380
I was going to lose it.

185
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:17,060
You won't.

186
00:15:27,110 --> 00:15:32,590
♪Tonight the rain falls soft and slow♪

187
00:15:34,190 --> 00:15:39,670
♪Blending with letters left unread
drifting through the air♪

188
00:15:40,710 --> 00:15:45,750
♪You turn and look back at me♪

189
00:15:47,190 --> 00:15:52,390
♪In those same eyes familiar tears
quietly appear♪

190
00:15:53,550 --> 00:15:58,870
♪It feels like we have carried so much♪

191
00:16:00,470 --> 00:16:05,630
♪So many questions time itself
could not make clear♪

192
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:12,070
♪The moment you walked into my life♪

193
00:16:13,550 --> 00:16:19,030
♪Every dream I had became something
I want with you near♪

194
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:26,390
♪How many letters have I written
just for you?♪

195
00:16:26,830 --> 00:16:32,190
♪If only you could truly hear
what my heart is trying to say♪

196
00:16:33,190 --> 00:16:39,270
♪From this life on no distance
could keep us apart♪

197
00:16:39,550 --> 00:16:42,270
♪The promise we made♪

198
00:16:42,430 --> 00:16:45,910
♪Will find its way
to be fulfilled one day♪

199
00:16:46,110 --> 00:16:52,510
♪But I want more
than just that fleeting gaze♪

200
00:16:52,710 --> 00:16:58,790
♪Still I have not heard your answer♪

201
00:16:59,510 --> 00:17:05,590
♪Can we still rewrite the ending
we face?♪

202
00:17:05,830 --> 00:17:10,630
♪When regrets begin to turn around you
will hear it all♪

203
00:17:11,430 --> 00:17:14,110
♪Everything that leads me back to you♪
